        <div id="warranty" class="tab-pane active">
          <h2>For A Lifetime</h2>
          <p>Our products aren’t made overseas in high-volume factories. They’re handmade with care in our small shop.</p>
          <p>That’s how we can fearlessly offer a <b>life-time guarantee</b> of our leather and canvas products for damages due to normal wear and tear.</p>
          <h3>Defining Normal Wear and Tear</h3>
          <p>We hate to get technical, but if you:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Shred your Slim Wallet with a weedwhacker, that’s not normal wear and tear. That one’s on you.</li>
            <li>Burn a hole in your Black Anchor Duffle Bag with an acetyline torch, first of all, how are you alive? Second, we can’t help you.</li>
            <li>Drop your iPad Notebook down an ice fishing hole while playing candy crush, and later dive down and get it after the spring thaw, we can’t help you.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>You get the idea.</p>
          <p>If, in the course of regular use, our product fails, we’ll gladly repair it for you so you can keep the leather’s lovely patina, or, if it can’t be repaired, we’ll replace it with a new version of the same product.</p>
          <p> Beware, our styles change through the years, so try to embrace change with an open heart – it’s part of the adventure.</p>
          <h3>What Counts as Failing?</h3>
          <p>We’re glad you asked. Look for things like:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Stitching coming undone</li>
            <li>Hardware falling off</li>
            <li>Leather disintegrating</li>
          </ul>
          <h3>What doesn't count?</h3>
          <p>Staining, scratches, gouges, etc. If your product takes on any of the above character, good on you. That means you’re living and we salute that, but we can’t replace items with superficial damage.</p>
          <p>NOTE: Since our lifetime guarantee is an above-and-beyond service, shipping costs for the exchange or repaired item will be charged to you, the customer.</p>
        </div>

